quran[96]{c,v,t}:
  56,1,When the Inevitable Event comes to pass
  56,2,there will be none to deny its occurrence
  56,3,it will bring some low and raise others up
  56,4,When the earth will be shaken violently
  56,5,and the mountains crushed to pieces
  56,6,and turn to scattered dust
  56,7,then you are sorted into three groups
  56,8,the people of the right – how blessed will be the people of the right
  56,9,The people of the left – how miserable will be the people of the left
  56,10,"And the forerunners [in faith] are the forerunners [in Paradise]"
  56,11,"They are the nearest ones [to Allah]"
  56,12,in Gardens of Bliss
  56,13,many from the early generations
  56,14,and a few from the later generations
  56,15,"[They will be seated] on jeweled couches"
  56,16,"reclining on them, facing one another"
  56,17,They will be served by immortal youths
  56,18,"with cups, pitchers, and glasses [of wine] from a flowing spring"
  56,19,which will neither cause any headache nor intoxication
  56,20,along with fruits of their choice
  56,21,and flesh of birds that they may desire
  56,22,"And [they will have] maidens of wide gorgeous eyes"
  56,23,like pristine pearls
  56,24,as a reward for what they used to do
  56,25,They will not hear therein any idle talk or sinful speech
  56,26,"except the words of peace, peace"
  56,27,The people of the right – how blessed will be the people of the right
  56,28,"[They will be] amid thornless lote trees"
  56,29,and clusters of bananas
  56,30,and shade long-extended
  56,31,and flowing water
  56,32,and abundant fruit –
  56,33,neither ceasing nor restricted –
  56,34,"and mattresses raised high [on beds]"
  56,35,"Indeed, We have perfectly created them [their spouses]"
  56,36,and have made them virgins
  56,37,loving and of equal age
  56,38,for the people of the right
  56,39,many from the earlier generations
  56,40,and many from the later generations
  56,41,And the people of the left – how wretched will be the people of the left
  56,42,"[They will be] in scorching wind and scalding water"
  56,43,in the shade of black smoke
  56,44,neither cool nor refreshing
  56,45,"Indeed, they used to be in luxuries before"
  56,46,"and persisted in the gravest sin [of polytheism]"
  56,47,"They used to say, \"When we die and become dust and bones, will we really be raised again"
  56,48,And our forefathers as well?”
  56,49,"Say, [O Prophet], “Indeed, the former and later generations"
  56,50,will be gathered on a predetermined Day
  56,51,"Then you, O misguided deniers"
  56,52,will surely eat from the tree of zaqqūm
  56,53,filling your bellies with it
  56,54,and drinking scalding water on top of it
  56,55,drinking like thirsty camels do.”
  56,56,This will be their welcome on the Day of Judgment
  56,57,"It is We Who created you; will you not then believe [in resurrection]"
  56,58,Have you thought about the semen that you emit
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or is it We Who are the Creators"
  56,60,"We have ordained death among you, and nothing can overcome us"
  56,61,from transforming you and recreating you in forms that you do not know
  56,62,You are well aware of the first creation; why do you not then take heed
  56,63,Have you thought about what you sow
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it grow, or is it We Who make it grow"
  56,65,"If We willed, We could reduce your harvest to crumble, leaving you to wonder and lament"
  56,66,“We suffered loss
  56,67,"rather, we are deprived.”"
  56,68,Have you thought about the water that you drink
  56,69,"Is it you who bring it down from the clouds, or is it We Who bring it down"
  56,70,"If We willed, We could make it salty; will you not then give thanks"
  56,71,Have you thought about the fire that you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who produced its trees, or is it We Who produced it"
  56,73,"We made it a reminder [of the Hellfire] and a benefit for the travelers"
  56,74,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  56,75,I do swear by the positions of the stars –
  56,76,"and this is indeed a great oath, if only you knew –"
  56,77,that this is indeed a noble Qur’an
  56,78,in a well-preserved Record
  56,79,"that none can touch except the purified [angels] –"
  56,80,a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  56,81,Do you take this discourse lightly
  56,82,"and instead [of thanking Allah] for the provision you are given, you show ingratitude"
  56,83,"Then why [you are helpless] when the soul reaches the throat"
  56,84,while you are looking on
  56,85,"when We are closer to him than you, but you do not see"
  56,86,"If you are not subject to retribution, then why do you not"
  56,87,"bring that [soul] back, if you are truthful"
  56,88,If that dying person is one of those who will be brought near to Allah
  56,89,"then [he will have] comfort, fragrance, and Garden of Bliss"
  56,90,If he is one of the people of the right
  56,91,"[He will be told], “Peace be to you, for being one of the people of the right.”"
  56,92,But if he is one of the misguided deniers
  56,93,then he will be welcomed with scalding water
  56,94,and he will burn in Blazing Fire
  56,95,This is indeed the absolute truth
  56,96,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great"